{
  "doc_id": "33758",
  "text": "Since its discovery in 2004 [CITATION_1] , graphene has rapidly gained both academic and industrial interest because of its outstanding properties, such as high surface to volume ratio, high aspect ratio, extremely low electrical resistivity, high thermal conductivity, and high mechanical strength and modulus [CITATION_2] . These fascinating properties have attracted extensive research in recent years with ever-increasing scientific and technological impetus.",
